Package com.github.shiftac.upartier.data

Class CountFetchInf

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.shiftac.upartier.data.CountFetchInf
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PacketGenerator, ByteArrayIO
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MsgFetchInf, PostFetchInf

    public abstract class CountFetchInf
extends java.lang.Object
implements ByteArrayIO, PacketGenerator
    When fetching posts and messages, the program is not expected to fetch all items in a single request since they can use up the network bandwidth. In this situation client should specify the number of items they want to fetch in a single request, and to let the server know about the range of data, data like timestamp or id of last item must be transferred. Also, when fetching posts and messages, we need to ensure that current user has permission to access the data, so we need to transfer the ID of user.

    class extending this class should explain the meanings of their type.

    When transferring as byte array: 

     class CountFetchInf
 {
     byte type;
     byte[3] reserved;
     int id;
     int count;
     long token;
     int user;
 }
